verbs.description: disnaturalize (third-person singular simple present disnaturalizes, present participle disnaturalizing, simple past and past participle disnaturalized)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make alien; to deprive of the privileges of birth.
examples: [he] […] having served his prince well both in Afric and India, and being ill rewarded, renounced his country , disnaturalizing himself as the custom then was
